data.exclusion_criteria:
Patients with distant metastases (M1) or concurrent malignancies at the time of diagnosis (except second malignancy of the oropharynx);

Patients with a previously treated malignancy of the head and neck or prior radiation to the head or neck;

Patients with any other malignancy within two years of diagnosis (excluding non-melanoma skin cancer);

Patients who received chemotherapy prior to staging at MD Anderson;

Patients who did not meet the staging criteria of interest (Stage 3–4B);

Patients with poor performance status, Stage 4B disease, and treated with palliative intent;

data.other_inclusion_criteria:
Biopsy-proven primary carcinoma of the buccal mucosa;

Patients who received treatment;

Patients who were previously untreated or referred for post operative adjuvant radiation

data.exclusion_criteria:
Secondary involvement of the buccal mucosa from carcinoma of the surrounding structures;

Recurrence of previously treated disease;

Not receive the planned treatment due to noncompliance

Patients were excluded if they had:
(a) treatment with palliative intent;
(b) metastatic disease (M1 classification);
(c) neoadjuvant chemotherapy,
or (d) missing information for vital status, HPV status, SM, or ECE.

